{
  "texts": [
    "The possibility of data breaches and auto-run authorized utilization compounds the concern.",
    "The ethical conundrum that the opacity of AI algorithms presents is fundamental.",
    "The need for more awareness among consumers regarding AI systems' decision-making and suggestion processes is common (Dwivedi et al., 2023).",
    "The absence of transparency can result in feelings of powerlessness and dissatisfaction among consumers, who may raise concerns regarding the fairness and impartiality of the marketing strategies utilized (Hajli & Bouraoui, 2022).",
    "Adopting transparent practices and establishing accountability is crucial for organizations implementing AI-driven marketing tactics Algorithmic Bias and Fairness Artificial intelligence (AI) algorithms, when taught on data that contains prejudices, have the potential to perpetuate and potentially amplify existing social biases (Pan, Lu & Wang, 2023)."
  ]
}